label: ExchangedDocument
comment: A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that is exchanged between two or more parties.

datatypeProperties.comment: The date, time, date time, or other date time value for the acceptance of this exchanged document.
An amendment purpose, expressed in text, for this exchanged document.
The date, time, date time, or other date time value of a cancellation of the exchanged document.
A code specifying a category for this cross-border regulatory procedure, such as the appendices of the CITES Convention.
The indication of whether or not a control is required for this cross-border regulatory procedure.
The indication of whether or not the referenced document is a copy.
The creation date, time, date time, or other date time value for this payment trade settlement.
A unique identifier, for customs purposes, for this consignment.
A textual description for the type of transportation waste recovery disposal process.
The code specifying the status for this referenced document.
A code specifying a type of acknowledgement document.
The indication of whether or not this exchanged document is presented in an electronic format.
A code specifying a purpose of an amendment to this exchanged document.
A code specifying a type of response requested for this exchanged document.
The date, time, date time or other date time value when the first version of this exchanged document was issued.
A global identifier for this supply chain consignment item.
A proprietary identifier.
Information, expressed as text, concerning the transport of these dangerous goods.
An issue date, time, date time or other date time value for this declared error.
A unique identifier for a language used in this exchanged document.
The count of the number of lines in this exchanged document.
A code specifying the purpose of this exchanged document, such as request or reminder.
A name or symbol, expressed as text, of a radioactive radionuclide.
A status of an offset processing, expressed as text, for this exchanged document, such as the process offsetted by this document.
An identifier for a previous revision of this referenced document.
The purpose, expressed as text, of this exchanged document.
A unique recipient assigned identifier for this exchanged document.
A date, time, date time, or other date time value of a rejection response of the exchanged document.
A remark, expressed as text, regarding this exchanged document.
A date, time, date time, or other date time value of a response of the exchanged document.
A code specifying a response reason for this exchanged document.
The date, time, date time or other date time value for the revision of this exchanged document.
A unique identifier for a revision of this referenced document.
A unique sender assigned identifier for this exchanged document.
The date, time, date time or other date time value for the formal submission of this exchanged document to a receiver by a sender.
A code specifying a subtype of this referenced document.
A unique trader assigned identifier for this exchanged document.
An urgency, expressed as text, of this exchanged document.
The code specifying the urgency for this exchanged document.
The identifier for the version of this exchanged declaration.

objectProperties.comment: A party representing another party for this exchanged document.
The approver signature that authenticates this exchanged document.
A binary file attached for this sustainability inspection.
The buyer signature that authenticates this exchanged document.
A contractual clause of this exchanged document.
The number of copies issued of this exchanged document.
The number of copies required of this exchanged document.
The period within which this document line is effective.
The first or primary signature that authenticates this exchanged document.
The fourth signature, also known as the third counter signature, that has been authenticated on this exchanged document indicating where appropriate the authentication party.
A note included for this document status.
The issue location for this document authentication.
A party that issues this specified declaration.
The number of line items for this supply chain trade transaction.
The location where this exchanged document has been lodged.
The number of originals issued of this exchanged document.
The number of originals required of this exchanged document.
A trade party that receives this exchanged document.
A document referenced by this acknowledgement document.
The second signature, also known as the first counter signature, that has been authenticated on this exchanged document indicating where appropriate the authentication party.
The party that sends this exchanged document.
A signatory authentication for this referenced document.
The third signature, also known as the second counter signature, that has been authenticated on this exchanged document indicating where appropriate the authentication party.
